<TEXT>
national guard members from at least 15 states many of them 
described as volunteers are joining or supporting the movement of 
us forces to saudi arabia governors and guard officials said 
thursday 
their destinations and exact jobs were not revealed but they 
included air transport and aerial refueling units communications 
specialists and medics 
the number of people involved ranged from five from south 
carolina to 500 from kansas but most of the states did not 
disclose numbers 
contingents were drawn from army and air guard units in arizona 
new york new jersey kansas rhode island delaware tennessee 
west virginia illinois north carolina south carolina texas 
utah washington state ohio and new hampshire 
although most of those going on active duty were described as 
volunteers the south carolina guards spokesman lt les carroll 
said that by just being in the guard an allvolunteer service his 
states five men placed on active duty volunteered to participate 
he said he wasnt sure if they actually raised their hands to be 
sent but should be considered volunteers 
a contingent of the 105th military airlift group of the new york 
national guard volunteered to support the movement of troops to the 
middle east gov mario cuomo announced late wednesday 
7 the 105th based at stewart international airport in newburgh 
has 12 c5a galaxy jet transports it is the only air national 
guard unit that has the huge aircraft which can carry 290000 
pounds of cargo it flew 48 missions during the us intervention 
in panama transporting almost 23 million pounds of cargo and more 
than 750 soldiers 
a second new york contingent of 40 nurses and medical 
technicians from the 139th aero medical evacuation flight based at 
the schenectady county airport was approved thursday by cuomo part 
of the 109th tactical airlift group they would provide air 
evacuation of casualties in a combat situation said guard 
spokesman lt col pc kutschera 
seventyfour west virginia air national guardsmen were 
mobilized adjutant gen joseph skaff said 
the pentagon called the west virginia national guard on 
wednesday night seeking volunteers skaff said within two hours 
we got all the volunteers we needed which made us very proud of 
our people he said 
the west virginia volunteers include medics nurses medical 
technicians and cargo specialists 
twentyone members of the 156th aeromedical evacuation flight of 
the north carolina air national guard volunteered gov jim martin 
announced thursday 
this unit is made up of personnel that run the gamut from 
