<TEXT>
the deployment of us troops to protect 
saudi arabia prompted an outburst of antiamerican sentiment in the 
arab world ranging from demonstrations to calls for a holy war 
against the united states 
the us troops were dispatched to protect saudi arabia in the 
wake of iraqs invasion of kuwait one week ago although the move 
came in response to a saudi appeal for protection it fanned 
resentment among arabs who consider it unwarranted interference 
arab nations have so far refused to participate in any 
multinational military effort against iraq and have concentrated on 
diplomatic efforts so far unsuccessful to peacefully resolve 
the crisis 
even before the deployment of us troops there was strong 
antiamerican feeling in much of the arab world because of the 
united states close ties with israel but the deployment brought 
an upsurge in such sentiment 
the head moslem clerics or mufti attached to the military wing 
of the palestine liberation organization declared that if the 
united states attacked iraq holy war is a duty for all moslems 
the ammanbased mufti sheik nader assad bayoud altamini said 
in a statement clearly aimed at the saudi royal family that those 
who ally themselves with the enemies of god the americans and the 
westerners and participate in the killing of iraqis are 
considered apostates and their blood should be shed 
in jordan where king hussein said he continues to recognize the 
deposed kuwaiti government the powerful professional engineers 
association called on all arab governments to form popular 
armies to confront the danger posed by the attempt of america 
to impose its will 
we call on all arabs to awaken from their slumber after seeing 
for themselves that imperialist countries stand together against 
the arab nation and its interests the group said in a statement 
a group calling itself the jordanian committee for the defense 
of kuwait urged volunteers to go to iraq to help president saddam 
hussein who has annexed kuwait resist any us attack 
mohammed rashdan a jordanian lawyer who is the secretary of the 
committee said the number of volunteers swelled following the 
arrival of the first us troops in saudi arabia he said he 
expected the number would grow to more than 10000 by the end of 
the day 
the united states and saudi arabia have said the american forces 
will act only defensively 
libyan radio announced during the day that thousands of libyans 
were ready to go to the region to fight against us interference 
in arab affairs 
in the yemeni capital of sana about 1000 people gathered in 
front of the us embassy and chanted slogans denouncing the us 
intervention but yemen the only arab member of the un security 
council joined in the unanimous vote thursday declaring the iraqi 
annexation of kuwait null and void 
the official egyptian middle east news agency reported an 
antiamerican demonstration was staged outside the us embassy in 
the sudanese capital khartoum 
critics claim the united states has no reason to intervene to 
protect saudi arabia because it has not moved to end the israeli 
occupation of the west bank and gaza strip which israel seized in 
1967 
faisal husseini the leading proplo activist in the occupied 
lands accused washington of using a double standard with the 
arabs why ask only iraq to withdraw from kuwait he said 
why not ask israel to withdraw from the west bank 
