<TEXT>
three mountaineers dismantled a hammer 
and sickle and anticommunist demonstrators wrapped a statue of 
soviet founder vladimir lenin in cardboard in bulgarias second 
largest city plovdiv 
other countries in eastern europe have dismantled the icons of 
the communist ideology that held sway across the region for more 
than four decades 
in bulgaria where the former communist party still holds power 
such deideologization has proceeded more slowly 
the official news agency bta reported that onlookers applauded 
as three mountaineers scaled the local headquarters of the 
bulgarian socialist party the former communist party to remove 
the hammer and sickle on wednesday 
