cabinet on thursday ordered the increase as of jan 1 for sugar 
beets sunflowers cotton flax goods tobacco and tea leaves also 
covered are cattle poultry milk and cream 
the measure was clearly aimed at encouraging farmers to produce 
more to help end chronic food shortages that have left many 
grocery shelves bare nationwide 
