<TEXT>
iraqs chemical weapons might slow us troops 
down in the middle east but are unlikely to claim many american 
lives arms experts say 
brad roberts a chemicalarms specialist at the center for 
strategic and international studies in washington said iraqs 
chemical weapons could not stop a us naval blockade or defeat an 
american defense of saudi arabias oil fields 
if ground warfare broke out between iraq and the united states 
iraqs president saddam hussein could use chemical weapons to 
attack us forces and to deny them access to certain terrain 
roberts said 
but to do it over an extended period of time he would need a 
lot of chemical agent and it would have to be packaged in 
artillery shells bombs or missiles and he would need the ability 
to move the weapons into place quickly 
those three things are difficult and its not clear he can do 
them roberts said 
iraqs use of chemical weapons against iran led to ghastly 
pictures of victims covered with severe blisters but most of those 
victims recovered iran has reported 
as of april 1987 for example iran had reported 27000 victims 
but only 262 deaths said seth carus a fellow at the naval war 
college foundation in newport ri iraq has also used chemical 
weapons against the kurds an ethnic minority in iraq 
john deutch provost of the massachusetts institute of 
technology and a member of the defense science board said its 
likely the united states would dramatically escalate the conflict 
if hussein used chemical weapons against us troops 
i fear to speculate what the response would be by the us or 
its allies he said 
the threat of chemical weapons could reduce the effectiveness of 
us troops forced to wear protective suits and gas masks in the 
fierce desert heat the authorities said but most said that 
wouldnt give iraq a very important tactical advantage 
there is a popular misconception that you have to wear the 
protection buttoned up all the time and thats simply not true 
said matthew meselson of harvard university who has been a 
government consultant on chemical weapons when the detectors 
show there arent chemicals around you dont zip up 
meselson said protective gear would make it seem 10 degrees 
hotter than it really was if the temperature is 100 degrees and 
the humidity 50 percent a soldier probably shouldnt carry a 
90pound pack for more than 40 minutes he said if he has to pull 
on a suit over his uniform that might be cut to 20 minutes 
it would be an annoyance but nothing to compare with the 
incoming high explosives meselson said 
deutch disagreed he argued that chemical weapons pose an 
important military threat although not a major threat to american 
lives 
even a few badly aimed chemical weapons would cause every 
ship every military unit to conduct themselves in a more prudent 
way and reduce their effectiveness he said 
iraq has known stockpiles of at least 1400 tons of mustard gas 
and perhaps 200 pounds of the nerve gas tabun since it ended its 
war with iran in 1988 said carus actual stockpiles could be 
several thousand tons 
under ideal conditions it takes 4 tons of airborne mustard gas 
or 2 tons of airborne tabun to kill 50 percent of unprotected 
people spread over about a third of a square mile carus said 
if the people are wearing protection the death rates are far 
lower he said and much more gas is needed in the hot dry 
conditions of the middle east where gas evaporates much more 
quickly carus said 
mustard gas and tabun work in entirely different ways said 
gordon burck formerly director of studies on chemical and 
biological warfare at the federation of american scientists in 
washington 
mustard gas is an odorless alcohol compound to which sulfur and 
chlorine have been added impurities in the first versions used in 
world war i gave it the faint smell of mustard it causes severe 
blistering but is rarely fatal 
tabun interferes with nervetonerve communication you cant 
see your stomach throws up you go into convulsions said burck 
but american soldiers carry injectors they can stab into their 
thighs to give themselves a dose of atropine a chemical that 
counteracts the nerve gas it doesnt leave you in top fighting 
form but it doesnt leave you dead burck said 
