<TEXT>
some of the heatresistant tiles on 
the space shuttle atlantis were damaged during a thunderstorm that 
trapped the shuttle outside a hangar for several hours nasa said 
friday 
atlantis was about to be moved inside when the storm struck 
thursday afternoon preventing workers from moving the shuttle 
until three to four hours later earlier in the day atlantis had 
been moved off the launch pad for repair of a hydrogen leak and a 
newly fixed columbia was rolled out of the hangar to take its place 
workers counted about 90 cracks or chips in atlantis tiles 
apparently caused by hail said nasa spokesman bruce buckingham 
nasa workers will fill in the small dings with a silicon compound 
each orbiter has 25000 to 30000 tiles which protect the 
vehicle from the heat of reentry into the atmosphere each tile 
costs about 2000 
a lightning bolt hit the launch pad during the storm but a 
lightning rod controlled the strike and columbia was not damaged 
