<TEXT>
here are thumbnail biographies of arab 
leaders including the heads of countries frequently in the news 
and all leaders of persian gulf and arabian peninsula nations 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
saddam hussein iraqs president since an internal purge in 
1979 the 53yearold saddam has a background in conspiracy and 
violence in the baath party underground of the 1950s saddam 
established a ruthless dictatorship which brought the longest 
period of stability to a coupplagued country after he came to 
power as strongman behind gen ahmed hasan albakr as nominal 
figurehead president in 1968 some 50 high military and civilian 
officials were executed twelve years later he launched the persian 
gulf war against iran thinking he would quickly vanquish his enemy 
because of the revolutionary chaos in iran he miscalculated and 
the war halted in a stalemate in 1988 leaving both countries 
ruined but iraqs war machine was built into the mightiest in the 
arab middle east and easily overran kuwait on aug 2 like many 
arab leaders saddam has survived several assassination attempts 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
sheik jaber alahmed alsabah the 62yearold emir of kuwait 
came to power in 1977 after a dozen years as crown prince and prime 
minister in order to lessen kuwaits dependence on oil revenues 
sheik jaber spearheaded the countrys diversification and oversaw 
its huge overseas investment program kuwait has invested about 
100 billion outside the country partly in a future generations 
fund by 1990 kuwait was making more money from its investments 
overseas than from its oil sales but the border dispute with iraq 
remained unresolved the nowdeposed emirs family ruled kuwait 
since 1756 the family allowed democratic elections twice but 
dissolved parliament due to harsh critcism of ministers from the 
alsabah family 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
king fahd ibn abdelaziz the 70yearold saudi arabian monarch 
is the sixth son of king abdelaziz ibn saud the founder of the 
kingdom fahd who has ruled since 1982 heads a royal family of 
4000 princes who are the cement that holds the kingdom together 
he is believed to the the worlds secondrichest person with his 
worth estimated at 18 billion in 1988 second only to the sultan 
of brunei said to be worth several billion more but the title he 
cherishes is guardian of the two holy shrines which is how he is 
always referred to inside the kingdom his highest duty is to 
preserve mecca and medina sites of the annual hajj or moslem 
pilgrimage 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
hosni mubarak the president of egypt a 62yearold former 
fighter pilot and later air force commander was chosen by the late 
president anwar sadat as his vicepresident in 1975 unlike his 
predecessor he eschews grand gestures such as sadats shock visit 
to jerusalem in 1977 caution has been the hallmark of mubaraks 
rule the president suffered a slight hand wound in the moslem 
fundamentalist fusillade that killed sadat in october 1981 mubarak 
moved to recover egypts traditional position as political and 
military anchor of the arab world a position it lost after the 
1979 peace treaty with israel the egyptian president has been at 
the forefront of diplomatic efforts to end the crisis triggered by 
iraqs invasion of kuwait 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
king hussein jordans monarch took power in 1953 as a 
teenager and has survived the tempests of middle east politics and 
numerous assassination attempts to emerge as a world statesman the 
54yearold hussein faced down a leftistinspired rebellion in the 
1950s rode out the 1967 defeat by israeli forces that robbed him 
of the west bank and crushed palestinian fighters in the 1970 
black september civil war following four days of 
antigovernment rioting in april 1989 hussein launched a 
liberalization drive that gave jordan one of the arab worlds 
freest presses and most open parliaments in 1978 he married lisa 
halaby the lebaneseamerican daughter of an airline executive she 
took the name queen noor 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
hafez assad the 59yearold syrian president until recently 
holding the title as israels most feared enemy seized power in a 
bloodless coup in 1970 he is saddam husseins sworn enemy in the 
arab world syria is ruled by a rival branch of the arab baath 
socialist party that also reigns in baghdad he supported iran in 
the eightyear war against iraq to the annoyance of most arab 
states a peasant boy from a minority moslem sect he rose against 
great odds to become commander of the air force and later 
president his declared ambition is to achieve strategic parity 
with israel and regain the israeliannexed golan heights in 1976 
he sent syrian troops into lebanon and 40000 of them remain he 
suffered a heart attack in november 1983 and cut down on his heavy 
schedule and stopped smoking 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
yasser arafat chief of the palestine liberation organiation 
the stocky unshaven onetime gunrunner has used both violence and 
diplomacy to push his palestinian peoples cause to the forefront 
of world attention the 61yearold egyptianeducated civil 
engineer cofounded the fatah guerrilla movement in kuwait in 1959 
his group rose to prominence through its guerrilla attacks on 
israel in the 1960s and fatah eventually became the mainstream plo 
faction in 1988 he got the palestine national council the plos 
parliament in exile to endorse resolutions that proclaimed the 
independent state of palestine and explicitly recognized the state 
of israel he also renounced terrorism and the united states 
initiated a dialogue with the plo broken off earlier this year 
after an abortive raid by a plo faction against israeli beaches 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
moammar gadhafi the mercurial 52yearold libyan leader 
ousted king idris in a 1969 coup and soon sought to acquire the 
mantle of his hero the late president gamal abdel nasser of egypt 
as leader of arab nationalism under gadhafi libya became 
notorious for its support for international terrorism and its 
leader famous for his maverick ways born to a family of nomads 
gadhafi often lives in a tent and has a dazzling wardrobe of 
traditional and more wayout costume that is a fixture at arab 
summits president ronald reagan ordered a bombing raid on tripoli 
in 1986 after the united states accused libya of backing a terror 
attack on americans more recently washington has accused libya of 
building a poisongas factory a charge it denies 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
king hassan ii the 61yearold moroccan monarch is a wily 
prowestern leader who often strikes independent positions in the 
arab world morocco and neighbor algeria were the first arab states 
to openly condemn baghdads invasion of kuwait like his jordanian 
counterpart he has been a frequent assassination target and also 
like hussein he claims to be a descendant of the prophet mohammed 
hassan a frenchspeaking cosmopolitan has pursued an independent 
course breaking arab taboos by meeting with israeli leaders 
moroccans say the king has baraka or the blessing of god 
despite internal unrest in the early days of his reign which began 
in 1961 the moroccan monarch has become something of an elder 
statesman in the arab world 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

