operatives that the agency paid at least 20000 in rewards for the 
alvarez abduction and continued to support the abductors and their 
families to the tune of 6000 a week in living expenses 
he rejected a government contention that the dea was not 
responsible because its agents did not personally kidnap alvarez 
the united states is responsible for the actions of its paid 
agents the judge said 
he noted that mexico sent three diplomatic letters to the us 
government protesting alvarezs kidnapping as a violation of its 
sovereignty when such a protest is made and a treaty is violated 
rafeedie said the defendant must be returned 
