robert campeau the flamboyant canadian retailer 
whose empire foundered under the weight of debt was ousted friday 
as chairman and chief executive of his own company 
the campeau corps board made the announcement in a terse 
statement from its toronto headquarters campeau remains a director 
of the company but his future remains unclear 
campeau is an entrepreneur who went on a multibilliondollar 
spending spree for american department stores in the 1980s using 
borrowed money expanding his holdings to wellknown names ranging 
from jordan marsh to bloomingdales 
but his us retailing operations staggered under the weight of 
this debt and sought chapter 11 bankruptcy protection last january 
he has faced further pressure because of additional debts which 
include millions of dollars in personal loans and the declining 
value of the stock in his own company 
