any future shortages he made no specific demands saying instead 
that americans everywhere must do their part 
his predecessors had to take much harsher action in 1973 the 
united states then as now the biggest consumer of oil in the 
world paid dearly for its insatiable oil thirst 
gas stations if they were able to stay open had twomile long 
queues of customers who sometimes waged fist fights for gas 
president nixon ordered stations closed on sunday and sales were 
rationed on oddeven days based on license plate numbers billions 
of ration coupons were printed but never used 
thermostats were ordered set at 68 degrees in the winter and 
the national speed limit was set at 55 mph to conserve 
the country went on yearround daylight savings time 
independent truckers outraged at seeing the price of diesel 
fuel double parked their rigs and halted shipments sometimes 
violently armed convoys of the national guard delivered goods and 
army helicopters patrolled some highways 
things eased when the embargo was lifted at least until 1979 
when the shah of iran was deposed and ayatollah ruhollah khomeini 
turned off his countrys petroleum spigot 
gas prices skyrocketed from 69 cents to more than 1 long lines 
forced a reprise of oddeven rationing and angry truckers again 
shut down 
president carter wearing a symbolic sweater ordered 
thermostats at settings that would save energy he also installed 
solar panels on the white house roof to heat water 
then iran and iraq began pumping more oil to pay for killing 
each other a worldwide surplus grew in the early 1980s and finally 
resulted in a tumultuous price collapse four years ago when prices 
plunged from more than 30 a barrel to under 10 oil was cheap 
and the energy shortage was ancient history 
that situation more or less prevailed until recent months when 
iraq began making noises about raising oil prices to repay war 
debts then the iraqis invaded oilrich neighbor kuwait aug 2 and 
threatened saudi arabia owner of the worlds richest oil reserves 
once more american vulnerability is exposed 
a nation with 6 percent of the worlds population drinks up 27 
percent of the worlds oil half of the countrys oil consumption 
169 million barrels a day must be imported 
thats a bigger percentage of imports than 1973 when about 
onethird of the oil came from foreign sources and dreams of 
selfsufficiency disappeared like exhaust fumes 
oil is the nations top energy source oil accounts for 42 
percent of us energy needs and about 63 percent of all oil used 
goes for transportation mainly the 180 million cars trucks and 
buses on us highways 
in 1973 47 percent of the nations energy came from oil about 
53 percent went for transportation according to the department of 
energy 
some things have changed 
since 1973 the reliance on oil to make electricity has been 
halved 
the average car got 12 miles per gallon in 1973 and was half as 
efficient as foreign cars today the average is 278 mpg but the 
trend in detroit is back to luxury gasguzzlers 
utilities pitched better insulation weather stripping and more 
efficient bulbs and appliances to hold down increases in electric 
bills 
the government established a stock of 590 million gallons of oil 
called the strategic petroleum reserve which hasnt been tapped 
yet 
but 40 states have raised the speed limit to 65 mph president 
reagan removed those solar panels from the white house roof and 
even the oil interests see a disturbing trend back to old habits 
as long as the price wasnt too high and the product was 
available nobody has been thinking about it said joseph 
lastelic spokesman for the american petroleum institute 
youre not going to save your way out of it when you have lots 
of cars lots of air conditioners a high standard of living and 
all those wonderful things lastelic said people are not 
likely to give most of that up 
