the public outcry over alleged price gouging has 
apparently lead more big oil companies to trim or freeze thier 
gasoline prices with some cutting nearly a nickel a gallon 
others said they were holding prices steady and promised to 
abide by requests from president bush and lawmakers to practice 
restraint during the rising tensions in the persian gulf 
