the oil companies have been denying allegations by consumer 
groups and politicians that theyve been using instability in the 
persian gulf as an excuse to drive up prices at the pumps 
the companies said the increases reflected a huge jump in crude 
prices on the open markets as well as the threat that oil supplies 
might be disrupted 
since the iraqi invasion of kuwait crude prices have 
increased approximately 35 percent and the openly traded market for 
gasoline supplies has jumped about 20 cents a gallon 
houstonbased shell oil co said in a statement 
although koach said many gas stations would be in a good 
position to pass on oil company rollbacks to their customers some 
experts said it may take some time for stations to actually realize 
any savings that is because gas deliveries vary from as little as 
once a week to as frequent as three times a week 
koach also indicated it might be hard for some station operators 
to lower prices now especially those who had been reluctant to 
pass on the previous price increases for fear of losing customers 
its economic suicide to bite the hand that feeds you said 
dennis decota owner of red hill union 76 station in novato 
calif about 35 miles north of san francisco 
decota said he had raised prices 11 cents a gallon since the 
iraqi invasion but more than half of that went to offset a recent 
gas tax instituted in california 
among the specific changes announced thursday 
texaco cut its gasoline price to resellers by as much as 3 
cents a gallon 
bp cut prices at its gas pumps by 3 cents per gallon 
conoco lowered by 3 to 4 cents its wholesale prices for 
gasoline and by a penny its price for diesel fuel 
getty froze gas prices for a week 
unocal froze prices until aug 16 
oil companies have been criticized frequently since gas prices 
soared from about 39 cents a gallon in 1973 to 53 cents a year 
later following the arab oil embargo prices climbed to 69 cents by 
1978 before surging above 1 when iranian supplies were cut off 
after its 1979 revolution 
more recently prices jumped after the exxon valdez spill off 
the alaska coast last year and heating oil skyrocketed during a 
severe december freeze despite allegations no profiteering or 
collusion by companies was proven 
in defending the price hikes companies have said that while it 
can take up to 90 days for crude oil to reach the united states 
from the middle east companies usually pay the market price in 
effect when it arrives at the refinery not the price when it was 
contracted for 
they also noted that large amounts of gasoline are purchased on 
often volatile spot markets 
</TEXT>
