system by any means possible sternad said adding that volume had 
decreased slightly by last week 
we will do everything up to and including getting everybody up 
to the chairman of the board to get our customers packages either 
returned to them or forwarded to where they are going he said 
the proposed contract calls for higher wages benefits and 
better working conditions sternad said it would raise the wages 
for the average ups fulltime driver a minimum of 150 an hour by 
august 1 1992 from 1610 
the contract also calls for a costofliving allowance of up to 
20 cents per hour each year depending on the rate of inflation 
sternad said inflation would have to be 10 percent for the drivers 
to get the full 20 cents he said 
parttime workers who start at 8 or 9 an hour would receive 
150 more sternad said 
company contributions for health benefits and employees 
pensions currently at 8300 a year for fulltime workers would 
increase to 10500 by the end of three years sternad said 
the proposal also offers a onetime bonus to be paid within the 
first month of ratification of 1000 to fulltimers and 500 to 
parttimers he said 
sternad said there has never been a national strike against ups 
which has had a national teamsters contract since 1979 but 
sporadic work stoppages and strikes have occurred regionally 
the mostv recent and biggest was in 1976 when 18000 workers in 
15 northeast states walked out for 13 weeks 
