<TEXT>
southmark corp emerged from bankruptcy friday 
transferring 75 million to senior creditors and shareholders under 
its reorganization plan 
southmark chairman president and chief executive officer arthur 
g weiss resigned friday as did the board of directors two 
directors agreed to remain in office for a brief transition period 
glen adams was named chairman president and chief executive 
officer of the dallasbased real estate and financial services 
company southmark announced 
adams who previously managed the liquidation of the great 
western sugar co will be joined by a new board of directors 
elected by the new shareholders of the reorganized company 
southmark filed for protection from creditors in july 1989 the 
chapter 11 bankruptcy filing made in atlanta and transferred to 
dallas listed total book value assets of 1046 billion secured 
debt of 1524 million unsecured debt of 1051 billion and other 
liabilities of 1909 million 
to comply with the reorganization plan approved by the 
bankruptcy court in dallas last april the company transferred 76 
million in cash along with new securities to various agents on 
behalf of southmarks creditors and shareholders 
holders of old southmark securities will receive their portion 
of cash new notes new preferred stock and new common stock upon 
surrender of their old certificates 
southmark also transferred 100 million in assets to its 
houstonbased thrift subsidiary san jacinto savings association a 
key feature of the reorganization was the recapitalization of san 
jacinto 
southmark will have no managerial control of san jacinto 
the rest of southmarks assets will be liquidated with proceeds 
being used to redeem the new notes and new preferred stock of the 
reorganized company 
the new preferred stock and common stock will begin trading over 
the counter on aug 13 
in order to ensure southmark has adequate working capital the 
company wants to defer paying an estimated 8 million in fees to 
professionals that represented the company creditors committee 
equity holders committee and the courtappointed examiner the 
fees would bear 10 percent annual interest from nov 1 1990 and 
would be payable no later than april 15 1991 
