<TEXT>
bond prices slipped friday in light volatile 
trading as participants took profits and fears grew that a war 
could erupt in the middle east traders said 
the treasurys benchmark 30year bond fell 1132 point or 344 
per 1000 face amount its yield which rises when prices fall 
rose to 879 percent from 875 percent late thursday 
the yield on the 30year bond due in august 2020 which was 
auctioned thursday as part of the treasurys quarterly refunding 
also fell 1132 point in whenissued trading 
traders said the market had little reaction to a report showing 
inflation moderated last month the government reported that 
wholesale prices in july edged down 01 percent 
analysts said the report which normally would be positive for 
the bond market was discounted because it occurred before the 
middle east crisis sent oil prices surging 
the market disregarded it as old news said kevin flanagan 
a money market economist with dean witter reynolds inc the 
mideast situation is not going to go away 
instead bond prices were sent lower by bondholders who sold 
issues to take profits after the treasurys quarterly refunding 
which concluded thursday said gib clark chief trader at daiwa 
securities inc 
in addition investors concerned that the iraqi situation could 
escalate were unwilling to hold large amounts of bonds over the 
weekend furthering the selloff clark said 
the market has been concerned that the turmoil and resulting 
rise in oil prices could heighten inflation which erodes the value 
of fixedreturn securities such as bonds 
also influencing bond prices was a rumor that the federal 
reserve would inject money into the banking system to lower 
interest rates clark said lower rates benefit bonds 
the fed did add some funds but only to make a technical 
adjustment in the monetary supply flanagan said the size of the 
injection made it clear the central bank had not changed its 
tightmoney policy he said 
the market was a little disappointed about that clark said 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds prices of shortterm 
governments were unchanged to lsqb point lower intermediate 
maturities fell from 332 point to 516 point and longterm issues 
were down by as much as rsqb point according to telerate inc a 
financial information service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman brothers daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer fell 098 to 115300 
yields on threemonth treasury bills fell to 761 percent as the 
discount fell 2 basis points to 738 percent yields on sixmonth 
bills fell to 764 percent as the discount fell 1 basis point to 
727 percent yields on oneyear bills fell to 765 percent as the 
discount fell 3 basis points to 715 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest rate banks charge each 
other on overnight loans was quoted at 8 percent unchanged from 
late thursday 
in the taxexempt market the bond buyer index of 40 actively 
traded municipal bonds fell 116 point the average yield to 
maturity remained at 745 percent due to rounding 
